(P.A. 19-117, S. 362; P.A. 22-118, S. 119; P.A. 23-141, S. 1; 23-204, S. 134.)

History: P.A. 19-117 effective July 1, 2019; P.A. 22-118 redefined “award” in Subdiv. (1), “qualifying student” in Subdiv. (4), added Subdiv. (7) defining “part-time student”, amended Subsec. (c) to change 36 months to 48 months, amended Subsec. (d)(1) by removing “full-time” and designating existing provisions re continuing to meet the requirements of the section and total leaves of absence not exceeding 6 months as Subparas. (A) and (B), amended Subsec. (d)(2) by removing “full-time” and amended Subsec. (e) by adding “and the budgets of the state agencies”, effective July 1, 2022; P.A. 23-141 amended Subsec. (e) by replacing “March 1, 2021, and October 1, 2021” with “November 1, 2023, and March 1, 2024”, effective July 1, 2023; P.A. 23-204 redefined “qualifying student” in Subsec. (a)(4), deleted “Not later than January 1, 2020, the” in Subsec. (b), “during the first forty-eight months that such student is enrolled” in Subsec. (c) and former Subsec. (d) re students taking a medical or personal leave of absence or being called to active duty and redesignated existing Subsec. (e) as Subsec. (d), effective July 1, 2024.
